We also investigated analytical capabilities of the N-Ti3C2 QDs/Fe3+ probe for GSH. As shown in Fig. 3, the GSH was added to the mixture solution, the fluorescence of N-Ti3C2 QDs recovered quickly, which indicated that Fe3+ was reduced to Fe2+ ion by glutathione. The Fig. 5
                         exhibited the fluorescence emission spectra of the N-Ti3C2 QDs/Fe3+ with 200 μM Fe3+ when different concentration of GSH was added. With the concentration of GSH increasing from 0.5–100 μM, the fluorescence intensity of the N-Ti3C2 QDs/Fe3+ gradually increased. There is a good linear relationship between (F-F0) (F0: N-Ti3C2 QDs/Fe3+, F: N-Ti3C2 QDs/Fe3++GSH) with concentration of GSH in the range from 0.5–100 μM. The linear equation is (F-F0) = 12.58 [GSH] +163.5 (correlation coefficient R2 = 0.998). The calculated detection limit of GSH was 0.17 μM based on 3σ rule, which is much lower than most of results obtained by other detection methods (Table 1
                        ).
